1. What are these Discs, that everyone has been talking about tossing at wizzards?<br>
<br>
&quot;Discs&quot; (disciplines) are abilities unique to melee classes at the 50+ levels. Each one has a duration (for example, 30 seconds) and an effect. After the discipline is used, it can't be reused for a fixed amount of time (like Harm Touch). Some effects include: being able to dodge all melee attacks, being able to riposte every attack, etc. Some disciplines -- such as rogues' Duelist discipline -- are extremely deadly, especially when used against casters.<br>
<br>
2. What are Golem Wands???<br>
<br>
Golem wands are items that used to drop off a golem in the Temple of Cazic-Thule. They have 5 charges of the spell Pillage Enchantment, which removes 3-4 buffs. Golem wands used to be insta-cast. That is, you could instantly get rid of all your opponent's buffs by clicking your golem wand on him a few times. Due to the recent nerf (they now have a 4-second casting time), they are far less useful.<br>
<br>
3. How many hours/days/weeks/years/decades does it take to build a 60th level Wizzard on Rallos??<br>
<br>
A lot -- I'd estimate 30 days played at the very least. Some Rallos wizards here might be able to give you a better answer.<br>
<br>
4. What the hell are Lures, and why have I been told there unresistable in pvp?<br>
<br>
Lures are 52+ wizard spells that are near-unresistable in PvE, and unresistable in PvP. By &quot;unresistable&quot; that means they always do their full amount of damage. So if I had a fire resist of, say, 150, Lure of Flame would still do its maximum 403 damage, while Draught of Fire (a more resistable spell) might do considerably less. As a consequence of their being unresistable, Lures are a mana-inefficient way of doing damage.<br>
<br>
5. What are AA Skills?<br>
<br>
AA skills are a way for 51+ characters to (roughly) exchange their experience points for new abilities. You earn an &quot;ability point&quot; each time you fill up your alternate-advancement experience bar, and each ability costs a certain number of ability points. An oft-discussed AA skill on this forum is Manaburn, a wizard-only skill possessing the ability to instantly kill another player.<br>
<br>
But don't level up a wizard with the intention of getting Manaburn. According to Verant, the ability of Manaburn to instakill another player in PvP is a bug that &quot;slipped through the cracks&quot; and will most certainly be nerfed in the future.<br>
